<Content>Loggiato dei Serviti very disappointing We stayed in the Loggiato dei serviti three years ago and had a great time. The hotel dates to the early 1500's so you automatically feel steeped in the history of Florence. It is close to most of the attractions and on paper fits the bill.Our second stay in October of this year was terrible. The booking process was difficult to start with as there are no online credit card bookings available.It took several emails, phone calls and even two faxes to book this hotel! There was no hot water in the hotel when we arrived. The staff were rude and standoffish when asked about it. The hotel was also noisy. The hotel overlooks a Piazzo and music is played there until the early hours of the morning. I had heard about this before we went and asked for a room at the back of the hotel. They assured me that there would be no noise from the hotel in October as the main tourist season would be finished at that stage and they gave us a room at the front which couldn't be changed when we asked. Our group got very little sleep as a result.The staff were very unhelpful when two members of our party wanted to make an international phone-call to the point of being rude. All in all a bad experience. We were glad to leave.We would not reccomend Loggiato Dei Serviti. 
