<Author>Chicpolitan
<Content>Small Gem The Loggiato dei Serviti provided my family with a cozy, comfortable, and quiet stay. As mentioned, there was entertainment in the piazza later on at night; however, the noise was, in fact, not enough to distract us from sleep. The staff was friendly, always making reservations for sights and restaurants alike at least a day in advance. I suppose it really does depend on the room you stay in, because we had a triple (one king in the main room, which happened to be quite large...one bed off in another room to the side of the bathroom). The bathroom in this particular room was a good size and easy to walk around in. The accomodations were very clean, which is always a plus. As for the colorful characters hanging around right outside in the piazza: just don't let it bother you. Granted, no one wants to go on vacation and hear remarks coming from driftersand other characters right outside of their hotel. But this kind of a situation could happen in any city. It did get a little tiresome, but don't let this scare you away. Walking up to the hotel may not be great fun, but once you step inside you are immediately transported into old world charm. Recommended, despite the inevitable characters that us reviewers have unanimously agreed on being a little displeased with. Thanks to the warm staff! 
