<Author>Teach4
<Content>Didn't live up to its pictures My parents and I stayed at the Loggiato dei Serviti in Florence for two nights. I chose this hotel because it was near the Accademia Museum and I thought being a bit towards the outskirts of central Florence would be better for us. When we arrived at the hotel it was in a big, empty square with homeless people sitting all over the stairs and benches surrounding the area. The smell of urine was pugnant in the still, summer air. There is a small door leading into the hotel, past a sleeping homeless woman.The staff at the hotel were not unfriendly, but also not very helpful. When asked a simple question the answer was not very informative.We went up to the room (I had asked for a quiet room) and were greeted with a view of an interior alley with piles of boxes and left-over junk. There was also a note that a mosquito plug-in would help ward off the pesky critters! We sometimes like to open the window to let in the night air-but this warned us off of that idea! The room itself was not like the pictures showed us from the online Venere. Instead of wooden beds with canopies, I slept on a dusty, couch-like daybed, and my parents had a metal, mosquito cloth curtain ensemble that reminded us of Africa or some jungle habitat. We were not impressed by the bathroom either. It was long and narrow,with hardly any room to turn around in, and had black mold in the shower. I have been to Europe many times before, so I know what to expect. In my month-long trip in Italy this was my least favorite accomodation. I would have to rate the Loggiata dei Serviti and being less than expected, and farther away from the center sites to be worth another visit. I have stayed in the Hotel Centrale in Florence and would recommend this central, modern hotel much more. 
