<Content>Excellent hotel but ask for the right room! As will be seen from the other reviews, this is a wonderfully historic hotel with beautiful common areas, but the rooms clearly vary considerably. We had informed them this was the second week of our honeymoon (for week 1 see Villa Accini in Monterosso) and we had a fabulous room, at the back so quiet, with drapes over the bed, fine bathroom, antique furniture, lovely view of the students from the Academia in their courtyard working on their sculptures. Breakfast good, barstaff/porters friendly, receptionists less so but helpful when asked. Make sure you ask for a room with a view and at the back of the hotel not overlooking the Piazza. Incidentally, coming from London we didn't find the 'characters' in the Piazza at all worrying, just colourful. 
